                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14100720" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 18 Aug 2014 15:04:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The code is actually not able to handle&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;select * from tbl where a in (&apos;a1&apos;, &apos;a2&apos;) and (b) in ((&apos;b1&apos;), (&apos;b2&apos;)) and c &amp;gt; 1;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;so I&apos;m not sure why that&apos;s not simply rejected. Supporting such syntax is actually &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4762&quot; title=&quot;Support IN clause for any clustering column&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4762&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4762&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but this requires refactorings that definitively won&apos;t make it in the 2.0 branch. So for now, let&apos;s just add the proper validation to reject such query (and add some tests) and leave the support of such syntax to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4762&quot; title=&quot;Support IN clause for any clustering column&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4762&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4762&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14118208" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Sep 2014 13:50:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem comes from the fact that &lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt; (b) in ((&apos;b1&apos;), (&apos;b2&apos;)) &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt; is a multi column relation. We do not support the mix of single column relations and multi column relations but have no check to prevent it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14118217" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Sep 2014 13:55:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch add a check to verify that the user did not mix single column relations and multi column relations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14118610" author="thobbs" created="Tue, 2 Sep 2014 19:46:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you add a test case to MultiColumnRelationTest to cover this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a nitpick, I think it would be a little clearer to use a couple of booleans (&lt;tt&gt;haveMultiColumnRelation&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;haveSingleColumnRelation&lt;/tt&gt;) instead of a counter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14119835" author="blerer" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 13:04:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The previous patch was wrong as it was not allowing to have a single column relation on the partition key and a multi relation on the clustering key.&lt;br/&gt;
It also take incorporate Tyler requests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14120177" author="thobbs" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2014 18:06:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
